1
00:00:31,198 --> 00:00:32,574
Hello.

2
00:00:32,574 --> 00:00:34,428
I'm Kim Hyun Jae.

3
00:01:20,789 --> 00:01:23,186
Why are you calling so early?

4
00:01:28,400 --> 00:01:29,756
Yeah.

5
00:01:29,756 --> 00:01:31,605
Thanks for handling it.

6
00:01:35,762 --> 00:01:37,955
Who's calling?

7
00:01:39,057 --> 00:01:42,617
I terminated my contract with PNJS.

8
00:01:42,617 --> 00:01:44,452
Why?

9
00:01:44,452 --> 00:01:46,268
Because...

10
00:01:46,268 --> 00:01:48,533
I wanted to be with you.

11
00:01:51,986 --> 00:01:53,572
How did you pull that off?

12
00:01:53,572 --> 00:01:55,999
It couldn't have been easy.

13
00:01:56,783 --> 00:01:58,742
The termination fee.

14
00:02:02,933 --> 00:02:05,482
I paid a freaking fortune.

15
00:02:30,792 --> 00:02:31,959
Hyun Jae.

16
00:02:31,959 --> 00:02:33,474
Yes.

17
00:02:34,655 --> 00:02:37,123
You're going solo this time.

18
00:02:38,380 --> 00:02:39,837
What?

19
00:02:40,919 --> 00:02:43,830
Khun's walking out on us too,

20
00:02:43,830 --> 00:02:46,819
and all we're left with is dead weight.

21
00:02:46,819 --> 00:02:50,420
This group doesn't stand a chance.

22
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:54,265
It isn't fair to make you carry everyone.

23
00:02:55,467 --> 00:02:57,206
I don't mind.

24
00:02:57,206 --> 00:03:00,659
We've all worked hard together for months,

25
00:03:00,659 --> 00:03:04,101
and Soo An and I have fans waiting for us.

26
00:03:04,101 --> 00:03:08,348
Wouldn't debuting as a group make more sense?

27
00:03:09,026 --> 00:03:10,674
"Make more sense?"

28
00:03:12,109 --> 00:03:16,579
I thought you were smart enough
to keep business and pleasure separate.

29
00:03:17,286 --> 00:03:19,860
I teamed you two up for better performance...

30
00:03:19,860 --> 00:03:22,251
but apparently, you've been dating.

31
00:03:25,147 --> 00:03:27,793
How many times did I tell you...

32
00:03:27,793 --> 00:03:31,128
to be careful because everyone's watching?

33
00:03:31,128 --> 00:03:32,751
Look at you.

34
00:03:32,751 --> 00:03:35,266
You have no street smarts.

35
00:03:35,266 --> 00:03:38,807
After watching what happened to Jae Min,
you still haven't learned anything?

36
00:03:38,807 --> 00:03:42,306
How do I know you and Soo An
won't end up in a scandal too?

37
00:03:42,306 --> 00:03:45,122
And you're still not thinking straight.

38
00:03:46,185 --> 00:03:47,936
Were you spying on me this whole time?

39
00:03:47,936 --> 00:03:50,530
You think I wanted to?

40
00:03:51,252 --> 00:03:54,174
I can't let my product get damaged,

41
00:03:54,174 --> 00:03:56,278
but you kept getting distracted,

42
00:03:56,278 --> 00:03:58,846
so I had to take drastic measures.

43
00:03:58,846 --> 00:04:01,459
The only reason you didn't end up like Jae Min

44
00:04:01,459 --> 00:04:04,016
is because I've been protecting you.

45
00:04:04,669 --> 00:04:06,612
Director Park.

46
00:04:13,504 --> 00:04:16,882
[Kim Hyun Jae's Text Logs]

47
00:04:16,882 --> 00:04:18,091
Hyun Jae,

48
00:04:18,091 --> 00:04:20,219
I don't like doing this either,

49
00:04:20,219 --> 00:04:22,680
but you keep acting recklessly.

50
00:04:22,680 --> 00:04:24,552
What else am I supposed to do?

51
00:04:24,552 --> 00:04:27,567
You brought this on yourself.

52
00:04:34,441 --> 00:04:36,040
Sir.

53
00:04:36,792 --> 00:04:39,156
I can't work like this.

54
00:04:42,749 --> 00:04:45,410
You people put on a little makeup

55
00:04:45,410 --> 00:04:48,933
and start thinking you're a big shot.

56
00:04:48,933 --> 00:04:50,606
Hey, Kim Hyun Jae!

57
00:04:50,606 --> 00:04:53,551
You thought you made it
because you're talented, didn't you?

58
00:04:54,612 --> 00:04:56,473
Where is it?

59
00:05:08,308 --> 00:05:09,709
Kim Hyun Jae.

60
00:05:09,709 --> 00:05:12,231
Want to see something funny?

61
00:05:22,760 --> 00:05:26,368
[Next Stage Final Scores]
See whose spot you took.

62
00:05:26,368 --> 00:05:29,492
[6th Place, Yoon Soo An]
[7th Place, Kim Hyun Jae]

63
00:05:31,513 --> 00:05:33,500
Congratulations, Kim Hyun Jae.

64
00:05:33,500 --> 00:05:34,960
Congratulations, Hyun Jae.

65
00:05:34,960 --> 00:05:39,298
Be grateful to the CEO, you hear me?

66
00:05:39,298 --> 00:05:42,384
Fate works in mysterious ways, isn't that so?

67
00:05:42,384 --> 00:05:45,228
You're pretty unfortunate.

68
00:05:49,391 --> 00:05:51,417
Look, Hyun Jae.

69
00:05:51,417 --> 00:05:54,042
Has listening to me ever hurt you?

70
00:05:54,042 --> 00:05:57,149
No one cares about you as much as I do.

71
00:05:57,149 --> 00:06:01,995
So from now on, just do what I tell you.

72
00:06:03,375 --> 00:06:05,134
Got it?

73
00:06:05,134 --> 00:06:07,659
Just look pretty, dance, and sing.

74
00:06:07,659 --> 00:06:11,040
You don't even have to think. How easy is that?

75
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:13,467
As long as you do exactly what I say,

76
00:06:13,467 --> 00:06:16,310
I'll give you the best of everything.

77
00:06:16,960 --> 00:06:18,590
So...

78
00:06:19,204 --> 00:06:23,917
Don't get any ideas.
Just keep doing what you've been doing.

79
00:06:23,917 --> 00:06:25,510
Okay?

80
00:06:42,277 --> 00:06:44,905
The song's so good, right?

81
00:06:44,905 --> 00:06:48,207
Because I really want to debut
with you this time.

82
00:06:59,060 --> 00:07:00,735
What happened?

83
00:07:02,680 --> 00:07:04,367
What do you think?

84
00:07:04,367 --> 00:07:06,476
Didn't you hear?

85
00:07:08,413 --> 00:07:10,213
You knew about this, didn't you?

86
00:07:10,213 --> 00:07:13,233
You knew!

87
00:07:13,233 --> 00:07:15,485
This isn't new for us.

88
00:07:16,083 --> 00:07:18,235
It's not the first time this has happened.

89
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:42,393
It's nice out.

90
00:07:42,393 --> 00:07:44,047
After living somewhere this warm,

91
00:07:44,047 --> 00:07:47,000
spending winter in Korea won't be easy.

92
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,468
Is it that cold?

93
00:07:48,468 --> 00:07:51,521
Yeah. Really cold.

94
00:07:52,206 --> 00:07:54,499
That's a problem.

95
00:07:54,499 --> 00:07:56,939
It isn't all bad, though.

96
00:08:02,019 --> 00:08:04,208
This keeps us warm.

97
00:08:12,034 --> 00:08:14,211
Excuse me.

98
00:08:16,542 --> 00:08:20,309
You're Khun, right?

99
00:08:23,211 --> 00:08:25,123
Who are you?

100
00:08:25,123 --> 00:08:29,134
I'm a longtime fan.

101
00:08:29,134 --> 00:08:31,386
Your voice sounded familiar, so I glanced over,

102
00:08:31,386 --> 00:08:34,181
but I was surprised to hear
a language I didn't recognize.

103
00:08:34,181 --> 00:08:36,689
What language was that?

104
00:08:37,322 --> 00:08:38,727
Korean.

105
00:08:38,727 --> 00:08:41,647
I didn't know you spoke Korean.

106
00:08:41,647 --> 00:08:45,359
You look happy.

107
00:08:45,359 --> 00:08:49,167
I know you've retired,

108
00:08:49,167 --> 00:08:52,241
but someday,

109
00:08:52,241 --> 00:08:55,506
I'd love to hear you sing again.

110
00:08:56,161 --> 00:08:57,412
Well...

111
00:08:57,412 --> 00:09:00,420
I hope you're always this happy,

112
00:09:00,420 --> 00:09:02,429
just like you are today.

113
00:09:06,375 --> 00:09:07,991
Wait.

114
00:09:08,658 --> 00:09:10,095
Yes?

115
00:09:12,834 --> 00:09:14,672
Thank you.

116
00:09:27,459 --> 00:09:29,453
Let's go.

117
00:09:29,453 --> 00:09:30,593
Where?

118
00:09:30,593 --> 00:09:33,575
I just thought of somewhere I want to go.

119
00:09:51,306 --> 00:09:53,520
Make a wish too, Jae Min.

120
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:57,159
Wishes made here always come true.

121
00:09:57,159 --> 00:09:58,527
Really?

122
00:09:58,527 --> 00:09:59,641
Yeah.

123
00:09:59,641 --> 00:10:01,059
Tourists don't really know about it,

124
00:10:01,059 --> 00:10:04,946
but it's famous among locals.

125
00:10:50,686 --> 00:10:52,623
What did you wish for?

126
00:10:54,146 --> 00:10:55,584
It's a secret.

127
00:10:55,584 --> 00:10:57,174
What about you?

128
00:10:58,373 --> 00:11:00,719
Mine's a secret, too.

129
00:11:06,112 --> 00:11:08,825
I'll tell you when it comes true.

130
00:11:21,819 --> 00:11:25,793
This is the last time you'll see me on camera

131
00:11:25,793 --> 00:11:28,163
as singer Kim Hyun Jae.

132
00:11:30,552 --> 00:11:33,447
To all the fans who've shown me so much love,

133
00:11:33,447 --> 00:11:35,989
thank you from the bottom of my heart.

134
00:11:48,041 --> 00:11:49,834
We'll now present

135
00:11:49,834 --> 00:11:51,837
how we came to understand our differences

136
00:11:51,837 --> 00:11:54,173
and made the decision to marry.

137
00:11:54,173 --> 00:11:57,718
Hyun Jae, where on earth are you?

138
00:11:57,718 --> 00:12:00,584
Hyun Jae, we're in the same boat.

139
00:12:00,584 --> 00:12:04,725
If either of us screws up
and sinks this boat, we both drown.

140
00:12:04,725 --> 00:12:06,518
If it works out, we both survive.

141
00:12:06,518 --> 00:12:08,042
[Next Stage Final Scores]
Got it?

142
00:12:08,042 --> 00:12:10,000
Director Park. Hurry up.

143
00:12:10,000 --> 00:12:11,273
Yes, sir.

144
00:12:11,273 --> 00:12:13,275
Interesting.

